View Cultural Object Data

Cultural Objects landing page (or dossier) presents aggregated information about specific Cultural Object details and properties, related objects and static text. The Cultural Object landing page is divided into tabs that contain specific information.

Cultural Object Header

Cultural Object header contains following information:

  1. Classification - the classification of the Cultural Object - Painting, Drawing etc.
  2. State - current Cultural Object state
  3. Object Number in case the Cultural Object is imported from TMS, or CS Object ID in case the Cultural Object is created in CS
  4. Title of the Cultural Object
  5. Artist

Cultural Object Dashboard

Once the Cultural Object is opened, the Cultural Object "Dashboard" tab is displayed. The dashboard contains aggregated information about specific Cultural Object details and properties, related objects and static text.

In the cultural object dashboard you can find following information:

  1. Cultural object details - displays information about the cultural object
  2. Ongoing activities - - displays ongoing activities like Projects, Folders and Tasks related to the Cultural Object.
  3. Images - displays the Images related to the Cultural Object
  4. Documents  - displays recent Documents related to the Cultural Object
  5. Recent Comments

To access more detailed information select from following tabs:

  1. Dashboard 
  2. Details - to check the Cultural Object details
  3. Documents - to check the full list with all documents related to the Cultural Object
  4. Media - to check the full list with all Images, Audio and Video related to the cultural object
  5. Activities - to check the full list with all activities, e.g. Project, Tasks, Folders related to the Cultural Object
  6. Exhibitions
  7. Archived Revisions
  8. System data - to check system data related to the Cultural Object
  9. Permissions - to check the applied permissions on the Cultural Object
  10. Versions
